metadata.test_query:
select * from (
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.monitors_runs
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.data_monitoring_metrics
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.alerts_anomaly_detection
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.metrics_anomaly_score
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.dbt_run_results
        
          
        

        
        
        
        

        
        

        
        
        
        
        

        
        
        

        
        
        


        
        
        

        
        
        
        

        

        
        
        

        
        
        
        
        

        
        
        


        with anomaly_scores as (
        select
          *,
          
    case
        when dimension is not null then 
    'The last ' || metric_name || ' value for dimension ' || dimension || ' - ' ||
    case when dimension_value is null then 'NULL' else dimension_value end || ' is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        when metric_name = 'freshness' then 
    'Last update was at ' || anomalous_value || ', ' || abs(round(metric_value/3600,2)) || ' hours ago. Usually the table is updated within ' || abs(round(training_avg/3600,2)) || ' hours.'

        when column_name is null then 
    'The last ' || metric_name || ' value is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        when column_name is not null then 
    'In column ' || column_name || ', the last ' || metric_name || ' value is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        else null
    end as anomaly_description

        from ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.elementary_column_anomalies_numeric_column_anomalies_zero_percent__anomaly_scores
      ),
      anomaly_scores_with_is_anomalous as (
        select
          *,
          case when
            anomaly_score is not null and
            abs(anomaly_score) > 3 and
            bucket_end >= 
    dateadd(day, '-2', cast('2022-12-29 11:51:01' as TIMESTAMP))
 and
            training_set_size >= 14
          then TRUE else FALSE end as is_anomalous
        from anomaly_scores
      )

      select
        metric_value as value,
        training_avg as average,
        case when is_anomalous = TRUE then
         lag(min_metric_value) over (partition by full_table_name, column_name, metric_name, dimension, dimension_value order by bucket_end)
        else min_metric_value end as min_value,
        case when is_anomalous = TRUE then
         lag(max_metric_value) over (partition by full_table_name, column_name, metric_name, dimension, dimension_value order by bucket_end)
        else max_metric_value end as max_value,
        bucket_start as start_time,
        bucket_end as end_time,
        *
      from anomaly_scores_with_is_anomalous
      order by bucket_end, dimension_value
)
      where
        anomaly_score is not null and
        upper(full_table_name) = upper(cast('ELEMENTARY_TESTS.ELON_TEST.NUMERIC_COLUMN_ANOMALIES' as varchar)) and
        metric_name = cast('min' as varchar)
          and upper(column_name) = upper(cast('ZERO_PERCENT' as varchar))

    'In column ' || column_name || ', the last ' || metric_name || ' value is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||

)

        upper(full_table_name) = upper(cast('ELEMENTARY_TESTS.ELON_TEST.NUMERIC_COLUMN_ANOMALIES' as varchar)) and

    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.monitors_runs
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.data_monitoring_metrics
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.alerts_anomaly_detection
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.metrics_anomaly_score
    -- depends_on: ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.dbt_run_results
        
          
        

        
        
        
        

        
        

        
        
        
        
        

        
        
        

        
        
        


        
        
        

        
        
        
        

        

        
        
        

        
        
        
        
        

        
        
        


        with anomaly_scores as (
        select
          *,
          
    case
        when dimension is not null then 
    'The last ' || metric_name || ' value for dimension ' || dimension || ' - ' ||
    case when dimension_value is null then 'NULL' else dimension_value end || ' is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        when metric_name = 'freshness' then 
    'Last update was at ' || anomalous_value || ', ' || abs(round(metric_value/3600,2)) || ' hours ago. Usually the table is updated within ' || abs(round(training_avg/3600,2)) || ' hours.'

        when column_name is null then 
    'The last ' || metric_name || ' value is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        when column_name is not null then 
    'In column ' || column_name || ', the last ' || metric_name || ' value is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        else null
    end as anomaly_description

        from ELEMENTARY_TESTS.elon_test_elementary.elementary_column_anomalies_numeric_column_anomalies_standard_deviation__anomaly_scores
      ),
      anomaly_scores_with_is_anomalous as (
        select
          *,
          case when
            anomaly_score is not null and
            abs(anomaly_score) > 3 and
            bucket_end >= 
    dateadd(day, '-2', cast('2022-12-29 11:51:01' as TIMESTAMP))
 and
            training_set_size >= 14
          then TRUE else FALSE end as is_anomalous
        from anomaly_scores
      )

      select
        metric_value as value,
        training_avg as average,
        case when is_anomalous = TRUE then
         lag(min_metric_value) over (partition by full_table_name, column_name, metric_name, dimension, dimension_value order by bucket_end)
        else min_metric_value end as min_value,
        case when is_anomalous = TRUE then
         lag(max_metric_value) over (partition by full_table_name, column_name, metric_name, dimension, dimension_value order by bucket_end)
        else max_metric_value end as max_value,
        bucket_start as start_time,
        bucket_end as end_time,
        *
      from anomaly_scores_with_is_anomalous
      order by bucket_end, dimension_value
)
      where
        anomaly_score is not null and
        upper(full_table_name) = upper(cast('ELEMENTARY_TESTS.ELON_TEST.NUMERIC_COLUMN_ANOMALIES' as varchar)) and
        metric_name = cast('null_percent' as varchar)
          and upper(column_name) = upper(cast('STANDARD_DEVIATION' as varchar))

        with anomaly_scores as (
        select
          *,
          
    case
        when dimension is not null then 
    'The last ' || metric_name || ' value for dimension ' || dimension || ' - ' ||
    case when dimension_value is null then 'NULL' else dimension_value end || ' is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        when metric_name = 'freshness' then 
    'Last update was at ' || anomalous_value || ', ' || abs(round(metric_value/3600,2)) || ' hours ago. Usually the table is updated within ' || abs(round(training_avg/3600,2)) || ' hours.'

        when column_name is null then 
    'The last ' || metric_name || ' value is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        when column_name is not null then 
    'In column ' || column_name || ', the last ' || metric_name || ' value is ' || round(metric_value,3) ||
    '. The average for this metric is ' || round(training_avg,3) || '.'

        else null
    end as anomaly_description

        from "ELEMENTARY_TESTS"."ELON_TEST_ELEMENTARY"."ELEMENTARY_SOURCE_FRESHNESS_ANOMALIES_TRAINING_STRING_COLUMN_ANOMALIES_TRAINING___ANOMALY_SCORES"
      ),
      anomaly_scores_with_is_anomalous as (
        select
          *,
          case when
            anomaly_score is not null and
            abs(anomaly_score) > 3 and
            bucket_end >= 
    dateadd(day, '-2', cast('2022-12-29 11:49:29' as TIMESTAMP))
 and
            training_set_size >= 14
          then TRUE else FALSE end as is_anomalous
        from anomaly_scores
      )

      select
        metric_value as value,
        training_avg as average,
        case when is_anomalous = TRUE then
         lag(min_metric_value) over (partition by full_table_name, column_name, metric_name, dimension, dimension_value order by bucket_end)
        else min_metric_value end as min_value,
        case when is_anomalous = TRUE then
         lag(max_metric_value) over (partition by full_table_name, column_name, metric_name, dimension, dimension_value order by bucket_end)
        else max_metric_value end as max_value,
        bucket_start as start_time,
        bucket_end as end_time,
        *
      from anomaly_scores_with_is_anomalous
      order by bucket_end, dimension_value

    


)
      where
        anomaly_score is not null and
        upper(full_table_name) = upper(cast('ELEMENTARY_TESTS.ELON_TEST.STRING_COLUMN_ANOMALIES_TRAINING' as varchar)) and
        metric_name = cast('freshness' as varchar)
